annotationA: Phenylalanyl-tRNA synthetase, alpha-subunit is a cytoplasmic aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase that catalyzes the ligation of Phenylalanine to its cognate tRNAPhe. Together with the beta-subunit it forms a tetrameric enzyme complex. This subunit provides the catalytic core
annotationB: Threonyl-tRNA synthetase, isoform A; threonine-tRNA ligase activity; ATP binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: threonyl-tRNA aminoacylation; neurogenesis
